Record Class TreePattern.Var<V>

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
io.jenetics.ext.rewriting.TreePattern.Var<V>
Type Parameters:
V - the node type the tree-pattern is working on
All Implemented Interfaces:
TreePattern.Decl<V>, Serializable, Comparable<TreePattern.Var<V>>
Enclosing class:
TreePattern<V>
public static record TreePattern.Var<V>(String name) extends Record implements TreePattern.Decl<V>, Comparable<TreePattern.Var<V>>, Serializable
Represents a placeholder (variable) for an arbitrary subtree. A pattern variable is identified by its name. The pattern DSL denotes variable names with a leading '$' character, e.g. $x, $y or $my_var.
See Also:
  • TreePattern.Val
  • Serialized Form
Implementation Note:
This class is comparable by its name.
